It has taken a while for the current boys to gel but it is now slowly working.
James, Wan Bisakka and McGuire have been great signings, meanwhile Fernandes has been a revelation and lifted everyone.
Ole at the wheel.

snippet.textDisplay: I won't get carried away until this team wins something and something big. Not the FA cup or Europa League but the Premier League and Champions League. Also becomes more consistent in big games and regular games. No game in the premier league is a small easy game but United need to start performing week in week out and hopefully we can do this and start next season stronger. We need to sign a two footed right winger and maybe a more solid and consistent centre back and midfielder. Squad depth needs to improve massively
